A couple of things about this proto:

1) I forgot to include Oerjan's suggestion to allow Groups and Contests
   to pay for priority increases. The change has been made in v1.2, but 
   there's not much point in reposting.

2) I'm not sure about the "Decreasing Priority" rule. I think it needs
   to be Plato-Pragmatised, but I don't know what would be the best way
   to do it.

3) I followed Steve's suggestion, and gave a 2 VT reward to the proposer
   if a proposal passes. I have not included a penalty if the proposal
   fails. Any comments?

4) I wanted the Promotor to publish the Proposal Queue each week, but
   to be able to do so without officially distributing the proposals.
   I'm not quite sure how well I've done that.

   Thinking about it, we would probably not want the Promotor to publish
   the entire text of every proposal in the queue, every week, but e   
   should be allowed to publish the text of yet-to-be distributed 
   proposals, (and required to when asked, by the FOIA).

5) The phrase "A Proposal is Emergency if..." is ugly :p. It would be 
   much nicer to call them "Urgent Proposals". 

And further suggestions for improvement?

Blob

