Steve Gardner writes:
 
> I assume that this is because General Chaos has succeeded in getting
> the loss of Salary penalty removed for failing to Report. All very
> well and good, but it does have an undesirable consequence. The
> Assessor, for instance, has a Salary of 3 VTs. Under the new regime,
> if e fails to report, he still gets this Salary. The penalty for FtR
> is only 2 VTs, so effectively, the Assessor will have made 1 VT
> profit despite not performing eir duties.
 
I don't see this as particularly undesirable.  Once the Indulgence
situation is sorted out (I assume there is a consensus to the effect
that Oerjan's original conception of there being a net excess of Blots
is still seen as what we should be aiming for), 2 Blots will be much
more significant than the VT penalty, so the fact that the VT penalty
is not huge doesn't seem such a big deal. 

In any case, the Assessor's salary should be reduced with the passage
of the Omnibus Reform Act (though I don't think I noticed this
provision; Scott?), because they will no longer be responsible for VT
recordkeeping.  

And finally, Officers can't afford to just ignore the Failure to
Report Infraction forever; the Infraction of Dereliction of Duty kicks
in after three successive failures.

Michael.


