Steve Gardner writes:

> I'm also skeptical about Indenture: it seems like a very complex
> response to a situation (Lawlessness) which hardly ever
> occurs. Remember how much trouble we had defining the abilities of
> Executors in Probate, when there were considered to be Executors?
> I'm sure we'll have similar problems understanding the relationship
> between an Indentured Player and eir owner. I'd much prefer the far
> simpler solution of suspending the voting rights of Lawless Players.
 
I agree with Steve here.  For example, are we sure that the rules for
Executors etc are stable enough to ensure that an Indentured Player
can't be made to rack up more penalties in the course of being someone
else's slave, and thus be Lawless as soon as their period of Indenture
finishes?

Michael.

