I don't like this RGB-like forcing of scarcity, I am afraid. I would
much prefer a more economic solution, and I can imagine three ways to
do it. Really the problem is that more VTs are entering circulation
than leaving it. So I'd like to suggest the following protos:


1. Increase spending: allow everyone to cast up to five votes,
say. This would reduce the relative value of extra votes like the
speaker's or those of the champion's reward, but apart from that it's
easy to implement: simply change the last paragraph of 206 to read

      Each Voting Entity has five votes on a Proposal, unless another
      Rule says otherwise. However, no such Entity shall have more
      than eight votes on any Proposal, regardless of what any other
      Rule may say to the contrary. The casting of any votes may only
      be achieved by the casting of Voting Tokens, as specified in
      other Rules.


2. Increase spending by abolishing presence (repeal 1715 and remove
the references to presence in the quorum rules). This is another way
to force more spending of VTs.


3. Reduce VT input - e.g. stick to VT stipends, but reduce them to one
VT for three proposals, maximum three, by amending 1684 to 

      When the last Voting Period on a Proposal distributed in a given
      Nomic Week ends, the Assessor shall pay out to each each Player
      who cast a vote on any Proposal distributed during that Nomic
      Week 1/3 as many Voting Tokens as there were Proposals
      distributed in that Week (rounded down to the nearest integer),
      or 3 Voting Tokens, whichever is less.


I'd prefer these to one-off reductions of the number of VTs, only to
see overall VT holdings rise again because the reasons for inflation
remain the same.

Kolja A.

